SIMPLE: motivation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: motivation
<hw>motivation</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or process of
motivating.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The mental process that arouses an organism to
action; <as>as, a large part of a teacher's job is to give students the
<ex>motivation</ex> to learn on their own</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> motive, need.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>The goal or mental image of a goal that creates a
motivation{2}; <as>as, the image of a peaceful world is a powerful
<ex>motivation</ex> for only a rare few individuals</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Motive</ent>⟦br⟧
